        "title": "Add EvoLink provider integration",
        "body": "## Summary\n\n- Adds a bundled `evolink` OpenAI-compatible provider plugin with `EVOLINK_API_KEY` auth, `evolink/auto` static catalog entry, and OpenAI replay/tool compatibility hooks.\n- Preserves EvoLink's literal provider-prefixed model id so `evolink/auto` round-trips as `evolink/evolink/auto` where OpenClaw needs a canonical provider/model ref.\n- Updates generated plugin inventory/reference docs, the labeler rule, workspace lock importer, and generator display casing for `EvoLink`.\n\nOfficial EvoLink docs used for the provider contract:\n- https://docs.evolink.ai/en/api-manual/language-series/evolink-auto/evolink-auto-quickstart\n- https://evolink.ai/model-router\n\n## Verification\n\n- `pnpm docs:list`\n- `pnpm plugins:inventory:gen`\n- `pnpm plugins:inventory:check`\n- `node scripts/run-vitest.mjs extensions/evolink/index.test.ts -- --reporter=verbose`\n- `git diff --check`\n- `.agents/skills/autoreview/scripts/autoreview --mode local` (final pass clean)\n\nLive endpoint checks:\n- Unauthenticated `POST https://direct.evolink.ai/v1/chat/completions` returned `401`, confirming the documented host is reachable and requires auth.\n- Authenticated minimal `evolink/auto` requests to both `https://direct.evolink.ai/v1/chat/completions` and `https://api.evolink.ai/v1/chat/completions` returned `401 unauthorized` with the locally configured `EVOLINK_API_KEY`; no secret was printed. This leaves authenticated live behavior unproven until a valid EvoLink key is available.\n\nOperational note:\n- Attempted to create the missing GitHub label `extensions: evolink`, but GitHub returned `404` for label mutation with the authenticated `EvoLinkAI` account. The PR includes the `.github/labeler.yml` rule.\n",
